<subSubSection id="B4A865738701C66B04A9FA54FAFDD997" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FC0D36F88701C66B04A9FA54FC7FD9E7" blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1783]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="CEC6EAEA8701C66B04A9FA54FEE4D977" bold="true" box="[198,341,1533,1559]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="3BB24D7B8701C66B0534FA54FE6ED976" box="[347,479,1533,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hovorodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="CEC6EAEA8701C66B0534FA54FE6ED976" box="[347,479,1533,1558]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Hovorodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D5F557918701C66B0589FA54FDE0D977" box="[486,593,1533,1559]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="3BB24D7B8701C66B0688FA54FAB8D977" authority="Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1830" authorityName="Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1830" box="[743,1289,1533,1559]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mallodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEC6EAEA8701C66B0688FA54FCE8D976" box="[743,857,1533,1558]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mallodon</emphasis>
Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 
<number id="4A7A24DF8701C66B00A3FA54FAB8D977" box="[1228,1289,1533,1559]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1830.0">1830</number>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs almost exclusively by the narrow metepisterna (largest width of middle region equal to at most, 
<number id="4A7A24DF8701C66B0107F98BFA2AD95C" box="[1384,1435,1570,1596]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="0.25">0.25</number>
times of length in males and 
<quantity id="3B4A9B1D8701C66B0588F9E1FD88D902" box="[487,569,1608,1634]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="in" value="0.3">0.30 in</quantity>
females). In 
<taxonomicName id="3BB24D7B8701C66B06BDF9E1FCF5D901" box="[722,836,1608,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mallodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEC6EAEA8701C66B06BDF9E1FCF5D901" box="[722,836,1608,1633]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mallodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the metepisterna are distinctly wider (largest width of middle region equal to at least, 
<number id="4A7A24DF8701C66B0648F9C4FDEAD9E7" box="[551,603,1645,1671]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="0.3">0.30</number>
times the length in both sexes).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC0D36F88701C66B04A9F93BFAFDD997" blockId="21.[151,1437,152,1783]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The concept of 
<bibRefCitation id="98234B098701C66B05E8F93BFDF1D9CC" author="Lameere" box="[391,576,1682,1708]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refString="Lameere, A. A. L. (1902) Revision des Prionides. Quatrieme Memoire - Stenodontines. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 9, 63 - 110." type="journal article" year="1902">Lameere (1902</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="98234B098701C66B0620F93BFD3DD9CC" author="Lameere" box="[591,652,1682,1708]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refString="Lameere, A. A. L. (1913) Cerambycidae: Prioninae. Coleopterum Catalogus (pars 52). Berlin, W. Junk &amp; S. Schenkling (ed.), 22, 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1913">1913</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="98234B098701C66B06F3F93BFD6BD9CC" author="Lameere" box="[668,730,1682,1708]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refString="Lameere, A. A. L. (1919) Famille Cerambycidae: subfam. Prioninae. Coleoptera. In: Genera insectorum. Belgique, P. Wytsman (ed.), (172), 1 - 189, pls. 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1919">
<number id="4A7A24DF8701C66B06F3F93BFD6BD9CC" box="[668,730,1682,1708]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1919.0">1919</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), that considered 
<taxonomicName id="3BB24D7B8701C66B07DDF93AFBE0D9CC" box="[946,1105,1683,1708]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nothopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEC6EAEA8701C66B07DDF93AFBE0D9CC" box="[946,1105,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Nothopleurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="3BB24D7B8701C66B0160F93AFE03D9B2" authority="Audinet-Serville, 1832" authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stenodontes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEC6EAEA8701C66B0160F93AFA2DD9CC" box="[1295,1436,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Stenodontes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="98234B098701C66B04F8F911FE03D9B2" author="Audinet-Serville" box="[151,434,1720,1746]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refString="Audinet-Serville, J. G. (1832) Nouvelle classification de la famille des longicornes. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1, 118 - 201." type="journal article" year="1832">
Audinet-Serville, 
<number id="4A7A24DF8701C66B051DF911FE03D9B2" box="[370,434,1720,1746]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1832.0">1832</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which also included 
<taxonomicName id="3BB24D7B8701C66B06D3F911FC80D9B1" box="[700,817,1720,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mallodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEC6EAEA8701C66B06D3F911FC80D9B1" box="[700,817,1720,1745]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mallodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as subgenus, is not inadmissible. In some species, particularly in females, the metepisternum is not distinctly narrower than in some species of 
<taxonomicName id="3BB24D7B8701C66B00BBF974FAF7D996" box="[1236,1350,1757,1782]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mallodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEC6EAEA8701C66B00BBF974FAF7D996" box="[1236,1350,1757,1782]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mallodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
